##I'm overseas | Shanghai doctor in the United States: Americans hung up before, and now panic!

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Although the medical conditions in the United States are very good and the distribution of medical resources is very even, under the special circumstances of the epidemic of new crown pneumonia, it is impossible to achieve unified management, and there is no upper-level command to control the operation of each, it's hard to achieve the desired effect.

Contributing Writer | stone

In recent days, the hospital has set up a special Drive-thru test near the parking lot, a quick test checkpoint, but the level of staff protection is hard to say.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I am a doctor in Shanghai and have been visiting scholars in the bay area of California since May 2019.

On March 16, six counties in the San Francisco Bay Area announced "Shelter in place, " a public blockade that required all residents of the district to remain in their homes for three weeks from March 17 until the ban was lifted.

So how have Americans been preventing the first confirmed case in the United States since Jan. 21, two months ago?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After the ban, the streets were deserted

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The restaurant was forced to close

It used to be all about "foreigners. "

Since January of this year, new outbreaks of coronaviruses have started in China, which have had a great impact on the lives of people throughout the country. In a foreign land, I can not return to their familiar posts and fight side by side with you, but still constantly concerned about the domestic situation.

Due to the large number of Chinese here in California, they still maintain very close ties with the country. As a result, in the early days of the outbreak, the Chinese people here have already started to take action. There are Chinese people in places where masks can be bought, such as CVS, Costco, etc. , have bought for oneself, more is to prepare to send home, support domestic family.

And in the early days of the epidemic, because the confirmed cases on the U.S. side were all imported cases, the CDC's focus of prevention and control was also to improve the screening of inbound travelers with a history of travel to mainland China, and to strengthen screening at airports, even in early February, non-us citizens with a history of living and travelling on the Chinese mainland were barred from entering the country, and travel precautions against China were raised to the highest level of "warning" to avoid unnecessary travel.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
That's the official line, and in fact, on January 31st, the day before Donald Trump announced the ban, I went to the San Francisco Airport to pick up a colleague from home, and I still didn't see anything that needed to be tested or guarded, there wasn't even a temperature check for incoming passengers. At the time of entry, there was a special CDC work area. After 10:00 a.m. on a weekday, the area was just a decoration. There was no one there, not even staff, as for the colleagues entering the country, they were just asked by the customs officers whether they had any travel history in Wuhan. There was no difference on Peace Day.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The still busy San Francisco airport

Before March, it was mostly Chinese

The government has repeatedly stressed that the risk of transmission is very low, just do a good job of personal hygiene, no need to wear a mask.

Every year from November to April, the United States is in the influenza season, common symptoms such as cough, fever, muscle soreness and so on will not go to the doctor, therefore, each hospital also does not have the special fever outpatient service, the school still normal classes, no one in the hospital wears a mask except for the operating room, where everyone shakes hands, hugs, and even takes it off when they talk to each other in the hallway outside the operating room.

The hospital where I work is a large private hospital. Very few patients with fever come directly for treatment. The professor of our department sees more than 30 patients one day a week. All of them are scheduled in advance, the clinic has separate waiting rooms for different periods of time and in order to guarantee the privacy of each patient. Therefore will not be like the domestic expert outpatient service entrance long line, the lively unusual phenomenon.

At home in full swing of the various prevention and treatment of the virus, the United States side of the feeling is "a non-personal high-hanging attitude, anyway, I have closed the entry threshold, the virus will not enter. ".

By mid-to-late February, as more "unexplained community-transmitted cases" appeared, the first Chinese to sense the situation was in bad shape began to act again. When they went to the supermarket, they would find, rice, noodles and noodles are all in short supply, especially at the 99ranch and Marina Chinese supermarkets, where fast food pizzas, large portions of meat and toilet paper still line the shelves.

Americans, who have been slow to notice the virus, don't seem to realize that it's getting closer. School Cafeterias, libraries, and other crowded places are just the usual place to wait in line for a meal, except for a notice suggesting frequent hand washing, party, chat, and... no masks.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Chinese-style hoarding, only grab large pieces of rice and flour

At this stage, except on weekends in Chinese supermarkets, we can see shop assistants and a few or two Chinese people wearing masks. In other cases, no one is wearing masks for protection. After all, in western thinking, people who wear masks are all sick people, healthy people don't need it. Many local Chinese have been afraid to wear masks for fear of discrimination.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The campus rally is still going strong

For US visiting scholars, we wear masks at work because we are often in and out of hospital operating rooms, which is not very visible.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
But in our daily life, we don't always wear masks as we do in China. The main reason is that the area is so large and the people are so few. Even if you walk on the road, you won't meet many people, the only safeguard is to avoid the rush hour and go to the supermarket to buy groceries.

3 months later, Internet lessons, less surgery, but not mandatory

The turning point came in March, when hospital staff and school students were already reporting confirmed cases, the school closed early spring break, started online classes and exams, and banned all Party activities on campus. The cafeteria at the school cafeteria has been turned into a take-out, and no one is allowed to eat in the cafeteria.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
All food is to be packed and taken out

The students in the lab were notified and the lab was closed until further notice. Hospitals are required to evaluate all scheduled surgeries and patients, minimize unnecessary surgeries and outpatient visits, and departments convert case discussion sessions to web discussions. But these are not mandatory measures, but scattered to the departments of their own arrangements.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
It's a real concern. After all, according to domestic experience, if a hospital can not properly triage confirmed cases, suspected cases and healthy cases, in the absence of specific drugs at present, will only further increase the risk of infection.

I think that although the medical conditions in the United States are very good and the distribution of medical resources is very even, under the special circumstances of the epidemic of new crown pneumonia, it is impossible to achieve unified management without the upper-level command and control the operation of each according to its own function, it's hard to achieve the desired effect.

The real reason trump and western politicians love to hype the "China virus. "
How did the World Health Organization's "whistle-blowing" timeline -- a window of opportunity -- get lost?
